She doesn't understand why
I had to rush off to Paris

39:19.148 --> 39:22.152
and miss our 24th
wedding anniversary.

39:22.318 --> 39:24.992
And I have to tell my
daughter why she's dying,

39:25.613 --> 39:27.707
even though there are
people who have a medicine

39:27.866 --> 39:29.868
that can save her life.

39:31.828 --> 39:34.547
Her name's Clementine. She's 10.

39:34.706 --> 39:37.300
We first discovered she had
Glazier's Syndrome when she was 7.

39:37.458 --> 39:39.210
So, basically,

39:39.919 --> 39:43.139
as long as she can remember,
she's been the kid who's dying.

39:44.173 --> 39:45.925
I'm sorry.

39:47.176 --> 39:49.520
That's not what I
want to hear from you.

39:51.347 --> 39:53.065
What I want to hear is:

39:53.224 --> 39:54.976
"Yes, of course,

39:55.143 --> 39:57.862
your daughter can have the
drug that can cure her."

39:58.396 --> 40:00.490
Followed by the question:

40:00.648 --> 40:02.742
"When can we deliver it'?"

40:03.735 --> 40:06.488
Well, I'm assuming you
applied for the Stage 3 trials

40:06.654 --> 40:09.077
and your daughter was rejected
because she's too young.

40:09.490 --> 40:11.584
Maybe I'm not being clear.

40:12.785 --> 40:14.332
I don't want her
placed in atrial.

40:15.204 --> 40:17.832
Seven years of wildly
successful trials

40:17.999 --> 40:21.799
is enough to convince me
that your drug will cure her.

40:21.961 --> 40:23.713
Three months of pills...

40:23.880 --> 40:25.974
and she'll be symptom-free.

40:26.799 --> 40:28.801
And how do you
expect me to do that?

40:29.594 --> 40:32.313
The entire program is under
intense FDA screening.

40:32.472 --> 40:34.019
Every dose is accounted for.

40:34.182 --> 40:36.059
Not my problem, is it?

40:41.648 --> 40:43.696
I'll expect a call from you

40:43.858 --> 40:47.579
within 48 hours, telling me where
and when I can get my medicine.

40:48.571 --> 40:50.494
The Mother Cell.

40:50.907 --> 40:52.454
How do we even know you have it?

40:54.994 --> 40:56.837
Have a nice day.
